It took me eight years and three tries to beat the game. On the first and second attempts, I dropped the game pretty quickly dissapointed by the lame gameplay (Otherâ€“Worldâ€“monsterâ€“bashingâ€“andâ€“shooting) and the clunky controls. I almost dropped it on the third attempt due to constant crashes in chapter 6 corrupting the savestate, but managed to force myself to replay that part using the backup copy of the savestate (luckily I was already prepared and made backups regularly).

What a game!.. Not sure about Deadly Premonition 2, haven't played yet, but the first game definitely deserves the â€œA Blessing in Disguiseâ€ subtitle.

[hr][/hr]

In summary, to complete the game I had to:

[list]
  [*] use DPfix for Borderless Windowed Fullscreen; the game hangs up when loses focus in Exclusive (Real) Fullscreen;
  [*] cap frame rate at 60 FPS (the game physics is broken at higher frame rate);
  [*] patch the executable to set the â€œLarge Address Awareâ€ flag (not sure if it really helps);
  [*] save a lot, I mean, [b]A LOT[/b];
  [*] back up the savestate (dp.sav) each 2â€“3 save points, immediatly after a save point (there is a nonâ€“zero possibility that the game will break your savestate on the next crash);
  [*] roll back to the previous backup to replay some parts of the game (two times the savestate was broken; two times there were gameâ€“breaking bugs);
  [*] use a crappy old 2nd gen i5/Intel HD/Win 10 laptop to beat one chapter near the end of the game â€” it crashes on my modern desktop PC despite all the fixes and workarounds.
[/list]

